        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="diplomatic" ana="b1">
                <p>ΘΗΚΗ ΤΟΥ ΑΒΡΑΑΜ <lb/> ΤΟΥ ΔΙΚΕΟΥ </p>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p>Θήκη τοῦ Ἀβραάμ  <lb/> τοῦ Δίκεου </p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Tomb of Abraham the Righteous (or Tomb of Abraham, son of Dikeos)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p> Abraham usually appears as the Greek Ἀβράμιος or Ἀβραάμιος in Christian inscriptions - authors note that here it is the original Hebrew form. They also take Δίκεοu as an attribute instead of a patronymic, as the name is "virtually unknown in Palestinian inscriptions" </p>
            </div>
